WEBVTT

00:34.547 --> 00:38.547
[country banjo music plays]

00:38.880 --> 00:40.880
[engine spluttering]

00:46.963 --> 00:52.963
<i>♪ And it's one step forward, baby</i>
<i>Two steps back ♪</i>

00:53.547 --> 00:56.172
[continues on radio] 
<i>♪ Two steps forward, baby ♪</i>

00:56.255 --> 00:58.255
<i>♪ Three steps back ♪</i>

01:01.380 --> 01:03.380
[wind howls]

01:03.922 --> 01:04.838
Well?

01:06.505 --> 01:08.963
Dead as our sales were last week.

01:10.047 --> 01:11.130
Deader.

01:11.213 --> 01:12.213
[chuckles] Great.

01:13.255 --> 01:14.463
Just fucking great.

01:14.547 --> 01:16.547
Huh! Yeah, shit happens.

01:17.380 --> 01:20.338
But somebody'll come along
and give us a lift.

01:21.338 --> 01:23.797
Nobody's gonna come down this cutoff.

01:24.297 --> 01:26.422
Nobody, except idiots like us.

01:27.463 --> 01:29.297
We never should have taken this road.

01:30.422 --> 01:31.463
[sighs]

01:31.797 --> 01:33.588
Radiator's done for.

01:33.880 --> 01:37.755
Did you happen to check the water
back in Phoenix like I asked?

01:38.922 --> 01:40.880
Yes, and it was fine.  

01:41.922 --> 01:45.422
Well, if it was fine in Phoenix,
then it wouldn't be dead now.

01:45.505 --> 01:48.255
No, don't try and put this on me, old man.

01:48.338 --> 01:52.713
You're all, "There's no stretch
of this land I haven't been to, son."

01:53.463 --> 01:56.547
Yeah, you're a real American explorer.

01:58.755 --> 02:01.213
Shouldn't you be putting that
in the radiator?

02:03.213 --> 02:04.755
It's dead, son.

02:05.088 --> 02:07.172
There's no coming back from dead.

02:07.922 --> 02:09.588
Not even for a Plymouth.

02:10.422 --> 02:11.505
Right.

02:11.922 --> 02:13.422
So, what do we do?

02:13.505 --> 02:16.130
[groans]  We can rest the night here.

02:16.797 --> 02:19.380
And just before dawn,
when the weather's cooler,

02:20.297 --> 02:21.755
we start walking.

02:21.838 --> 02:22.922
Walking?

02:23.172 --> 02:25.047
All the way back to the last station?

02:25.422 --> 02:26.255
Yep.

02:28.547 --> 02:30.380
That's great. [sighs]

02:32.213 --> 02:34.838
That's just... [shouting] fucking great!

02:36.047 --> 02:38.047
<i>♪ Down ♪</i>

02:38.380 --> 02:43.297
<i>♪ Don't you lay your body down ♪</i>

02:44.005 --> 02:48.172
<i>♪ Don't you lay your body  </i>♪

02:49.005 --> 02:50.505
<i>♪ Down ♪</i>

02:50.588 --> 02:52.338
<i>♪ Mm-hmm. </i>♪

02:55.880 --> 02:57.963
[wind howling]

03:07.797 --> 03:10.963
I'm sorry about earlier.
It wasn't your fault.

03:12.380 --> 03:14.338
I just get bitter sometimes.

03:15.505 --> 03:18.880
The days of the door-to-door salesman
are fadin' fast.

03:20.255 --> 03:21.297
[chuckling] Come on.

03:22.588 --> 03:23.797
You know what I think?

03:24.172 --> 03:25.630
It's all in the attitude.

03:25.963 --> 03:28.505
The right attitude can sell anything.

03:28.588 --> 03:30.922
Well, you certainly got plenty of that.

03:48.963 --> 03:50.880
Reminds me of the sea.

03:51.130 --> 03:52.338
Never seen the ocean.

03:52.838 --> 03:54.463
Have to take your word for it.

03:55.297 --> 03:59.672
Did you know that millions of years ago,
this desert was a sea bottom?

04:02.088 --> 04:07.047
All of this was water,
full of fantastical creatures.

04:09.005 --> 04:11.005
The world's an old place.

04:12.838 --> 04:16.005
And for a long time,
it was nothing but sea.

04:20.922 --> 04:23.630
Nights like this, it gets me wonderin':

04:24.547 --> 04:27.713
If the ghosts of people
can haunt a house,

04:28.380 --> 04:32.255
well, why can't the ghosts of creatures
haunt where they once lived?

04:32.422 --> 04:35.713
[laughs] I have no idea what the hell
you're talking about.

04:36.130 --> 04:37.922
[yawns] I'm gonna sleep in the back seat.

04:38.672 --> 04:40.130
You can take the front.

04:43.963 --> 04:45.880
It must have been nice back then.

04:46.297 --> 04:49.588
Just swimming around
without a care in the world.

05:06.588 --> 05:08.588
[electrical buzz]

05:10.505 --> 05:12.672
[radio static]

05:21.838 --> 05:23.838
[whale singing]

05:25.505 --> 05:26.422
What?

05:29.338 --> 05:30.463
[gasps]

05:36.422 --> 05:38.005
-[whispering] Wake up.
-What?

05:38.088 --> 05:40.130
Shhhh.  Look.

05:43.172 --> 05:44.505
[younger man] Holy shit!

05:46.047 --> 05:47.213
[laughs] Wow!

05:49.338 --> 05:50.838
You ever seen anything like this?

05:51.213 --> 05:52.338
Never.

05:54.755 --> 05:56.005
[younger man laughs]

06:20.713 --> 06:21.755
[younger man] It's...

06:23.422 --> 06:25.005
It's beautiful.

06:28.713 --> 06:30.463
It must be something like you said.

06:32.005 --> 06:33.922
Ghosts of an older world.

06:38.005 --> 06:39.088
Boo!

06:39.547 --> 06:41.755
[laughs] Did you see that?

06:42.380 --> 06:44.588
-Hey.  
-Oh, my God! [laughs]

06:45.547 --> 06:47.088
I can feel them!

06:47.172 --> 06:48.338
[laughs]

06:49.088 --> 06:50.172
This is so cool.

06:50.255 --> 06:52.213
Hey, hold on a second, boy.

06:55.880 --> 06:57.088
[laughs]

06:58.422 --> 06:59.797
What are you doing?

07:02.463 --> 07:03.963
[laughs]

07:05.588 --> 07:06.963
[shouts] I'm going up there!

07:09.422 --> 07:10.755
[shouts]  Don't be crazy!

07:10.838 --> 07:14.380
[younger man shouts] I wanna swim!
[laughs]

07:31.297 --> 07:32.130
[chuckles]

07:32.213 --> 07:34.213
Hey, come back down here!

07:36.338 --> 07:37.213
What?

07:43.088 --> 07:44.338
[older man shouts] Hey!

07:45.047 --> 07:47.880
Look, behind you! Look!

07:49.213 --> 07:51.755
Hey! Look!

07:52.422 --> 07:54.213
Goddamn fool!

07:54.463 --> 07:55.547
Look out!

08:00.338 --> 08:01.505
Behind you!

08:01.588 --> 08:03.755
Look!

08:08.588 --> 08:09.672
[gasps]

08:20.963 --> 08:23.672
[folk music plays]
